      "title": "Delaunay triangulation, convex hulls, and Voronoi diagrams"
    },
    {
      "children": [],
      "title": "Plotting helpers"
    },
    {
      "children": [
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "The simplices (triangles, tetrahedra, etc.) appearing in the Delaunay tessellation (N - D simplices), convex hull facets, and Voronoi ridges (N - 1 - D simplices) are represented in the following scheme "
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": [
              {
                "type": "BlockVerbatim",
                "data": {
                  "lines": {
                    "_lines": [
                      {
                        "_line": "tess = Delaunay(points)",
                        "_number": 0,
                        "_offset": 0
                      },
                      {
                        "_line": "hull = ConvexHull(points)",
                        "_number": 1,
                        "_offset": 0
                      },
                      {
                        "_line": "voro = Voronoi(points)",
                        "_number": 2,
                        "_offset": 0
                      },
                      {
                        "_line": "",
                        "_number": 3,
                        "_offset": 0
                      },
                      {
                        "_line": "# coordinates of the jth vertex of the ith simplex",
                        "_number": 4,
                        "_offset": 0
                      },
                      {
                        "_line": "tess.points[tess.simplices[i, j], :]        # tessellation element",
                        "_number": 5,
                        "_offset": 0
                      },
                      {
                        "_line": "hull.points[hull.simplices[i, j], :]        # convex hull facet",
                        "_number": 6,
                        "_offset": 0
                      },
                      {
                        "_line": "voro.vertices[voro.ridge_vertices[i, j], :] # ridge between Voronoi cells",
                        "_number": 7,
                        "_offset": 0
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "For Delaunay triangulations and convex hulls, the neighborhood structure of the simplices satisfies the condition : "
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Verbatim",
                "data": {
                  "value": [
                    "tess.neighbors[i,j]"
                  ]
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": " is the neighboring simplex of the ith simplex, opposite to the "
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Verbatim",
                "data": {
                  "value": [
                    "j"
                  ]
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": " - vertex. It is - 1 in case of no neighbor. "
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "Convex hull facets also define a hyperplane equation "
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": [
              {
                "type": "BlockVerbatim",
                "data": {
                  "lines": {
                    "_lines": [
                      {
                        "_line": "(hull.equations[i,:-1] * coord).sum() + hull.equations[i,-1] == 0",
                        "_number": 0,
                        "_offset": 0
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "Similar hyperplane equations for the Delaunay triangulation correspond to the convex hull facets on the corresponding N+1 - D paraboloid. "
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "Paragraph",
          "data": {
            "inline": [
              {
                "type": "Words",
                "data": {
                  "value": "The Delaunay triangulation objects offer a method for locating the simplex containing a given point, and barycentric coordinate computations. "
                }
              }
            ],
            "inner": []
          }
        }
      ],
